WEBVTT

1
00:03:11.636 --> 00:03:14.002
Hi. I've got an appointment
with Mr. Ullman.

2
00:03:14.206 --> 00:03:16.140
My name is Jack Torrance.

3
00:03:16.341 --> 00:03:18.866
His office is the first door
on the left.

4
00:03:19.077 --> 00:03:20.305
Thank you.

5
00:03:37.662 --> 00:03:38.526
Mr. Ullman?

6
00:03:38.730 --> 00:03:39.992
I'm Jack Torrance.

7
00:03:40.198 --> 00:03:42.166
Come on in. Jack.

8
00:03:43.268 --> 00:03:45.793
- Very nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

9
00:03:46.004 --> 00:03:47.528
This is my secretary. Susie.

10
00:03:47.939 --> 00:03:50.430
- Susie. how do you do?
- Any trouble finding us?

11
00:03:50.642 --> 00:03:53.475
No problem at all.
I made the trip in 3 1 /2 hours.

12
00:03:53.678 --> 00:03:55.578
That's very good time.

13
00:03:55.914 --> 00:03:57.506
Sit down a minute. Jack.

14
00:03:57.749 --> 00:03:59.512
Just make yourself at home.

15
00:03:59.718 --> 00:04:00.980
Like some coffee?

16
00:04:01.186 --> 00:04:03.677
If you're having some.
I wouldn't mind. Thanks.

17
00:04:03.889 --> 00:04:04.878
- Susie.
- Sure.

18
00:04:05.090 --> 00:04:06.819
And ask Bill Watson to join us.

19
00:04:07.025 --> 00:04:08.458
Yes. I will.

20
00:04:19.337 --> 00:04:20.463
Mom?

21
00:04:21.339 --> 00:04:22.499
Yeah?

22
00:04:22.908 --> 00:04:26.537
Do you really want to go and live
in that hotel for the winter?

23
00:04:27.145 --> 00:04:28.510
Sure I do.

24
00:04:28.713 --> 00:04:30.647
It'll be lots of fun.

25
00:04:32.517 --> 00:04:34.610
Yeah. I guess so.

26
00:04:34.820 --> 00:04:38.984
Anyway. there's hardly anybody
to play with around here.

27
00:04:39.791 --> 00:04:43.283
I know. It always takes
a little time to make new friends.

28
00:04:44.896 --> 00:04:47.194
Yeah. I guess so.

29
00:04:47.966 --> 00:04:48.990
What about Tony?

30
00:04:49.201 --> 00:04:51.465
He's looking forward
to the hotel. I bet.

31
00:04:52.137 --> 00:04:54.503
No. I ain't. Mrs. Torrance.

32
00:04:54.906 --> 00:04:57.204
Now. come on. Tony.
Don't be silly.

33
00:04:57.742 --> 00:04:59.573
I don't want to go there.

34
00:05:00.212 --> 00:05:02.146
How come you don't want to go?

35
00:05:02.480 --> 00:05:04.380
I just don't.

36
00:05:04.649 --> 00:05:07.447
Did they give you
any idea in Denver...

37
00:05:07.652 --> 00:05:09.313
...about what the job entails?

38
00:05:09.521 --> 00:05:11.614
Only in a very general way.

39
00:05:14.092 --> 00:05:16.686
The winters can be
fantastically cruel.

40
00:05:16.895 --> 00:05:20.353
The basic idea is to cope
with the very costly damage...

41
00:05:20.565 --> 00:05:22.556
...and depreciation
which can occur.

42
00:05:22.767 --> 00:05:25.201
This consists mainly
of running the boiler...

43
00:05:25.403 --> 00:05:29.362
...heating different parts of the
hotel on a daily rotating basis...

44
00:05:29.574 --> 00:05:32.099
...repairing damage as it occurs...

45
00:05:32.310 --> 00:05:35.302
...and doing repairs so the
elements can't get a foothold.

46
00:05:36.381 --> 00:05:38.542
That sounds fine to me.

47
00:05:39.017 --> 00:05:41.986
Physically. it's not
a very demanding job.

48
00:05:42.187 --> 00:05:45.350
The only thing that can get a bit
trying here during the winter...

49
00:05:45.523 --> 00:05:48.014
...is a tremendous sense
of isolation.

50
00:05:49.294 --> 00:05:53.856
That just happens to be
exactly what I'm looking for.

51
00:05:54.199 --> 00:05:57.327
I'm outlining a new
writing project.

52
00:05:57.636 --> 00:06:00.935
Five months of peace
is just what I want.

53
00:06:01.706 --> 00:06:03.435
That's very good. Jack.

54
00:06:03.742 --> 00:06:06.905
Because. for some people...

55
00:06:07.112 --> 00:06:08.875
...solitude...

56
00:06:09.080 --> 00:06:10.707
...and isolation...

57
00:06:11.583 --> 00:06:13.847
...can. of itself. become a problem.

58
00:06:14.653 --> 00:06:16.245
Not for me.

59
00:06:16.788 --> 00:06:20.019
How about your wife and son?
Do you think they'll take to it?

60
00:06:21.826 --> 00:06:22.986
They'll love it.

61
00:06:23.194 --> 00:06:24.388
Great.

62
00:06:27.299 --> 00:06:30.530
Before I turn you over to Bill...

63
00:06:30.735 --> 00:06:34.227
...there's one other thing I think
we should talk about.

64
00:06:34.439 --> 00:06:35.872
Not to sound melodramatic...

65
00:06:36.074 --> 00:06:38.634
...but it's been known to
give a few people...

66
00:06:38.843 --> 00:06:41.038
...second thoughts about the job.

67
00:06:41.746 --> 00:06:43.407
I'm intrigued.

68
00:06:43.615 --> 00:06:45.947
I don't suppose they
said anything in Denver...

69
00:06:46.151 --> 00:06:50.110
...about the tragedy we had up here
during the winter of 1 970.

70
00:06:50.722 --> 00:06:52.713
I don't believe they did.

71
00:06:55.293 --> 00:06:56.988
My predecessor in this job...

72
00:06:57.729 --> 00:07:00.960
...hired a man named Charles Grady
as the winter caretaker.

73
00:07:01.166 --> 00:07:04.693
He came up with his wife and
two little girls of about 8 and 10.

74
00:07:04.903 --> 00:07:07.895
He had a good employment record.
good references.

75
00:07:08.106 --> 00:07:10.370
And from what I've been told.
he seemed...

76
00:07:10.575 --> 00:07:13.271
...like a completely
normal individual.

77
00:07:13.478 --> 00:07:15.844
But at some point
during the winter...

78
00:07:16.047 --> 00:07:19.676
...he must have suffered some kind
of a complete mental breakdown.

79
00:07:19.884 --> 00:07:22.250
He ran amuck...

80
00:07:25.657 --> 00:07:27.852
...and killed his family
with an ax.

81
00:07:29.127 --> 00:07:33.757
Stacked them neatly in a room
in the west wing. and then...

82
00:07:34.566 --> 00:07:38.263
...he put both barrels
of his shotgun in his mouth.

83
00:07:39.504 --> 00:07:41.301
The police thought...

84
00:07:41.506 --> 00:07:45.567
...that it was what the old-timers
used to call cabin fever.

85
00:07:45.777 --> 00:07:48.803
A kind of claustrophobic reaction
which can occur...

86
00:07:49.014 --> 00:07:53.144
...when people are shut in together
over long periods of time.

87
00:07:58.223 --> 00:07:59.656
That is...

88
00:07:59.858 --> 00:08:01.382
...quite a story.

89
00:08:02.694 --> 00:08:04.161
Yeah. it is.

90
00:08:05.263 --> 00:08:08.562
It's still hard for me to believe
it actually happened here.

91
00:08:08.900 --> 00:08:10.595
But it did.

92
00:08:12.370 --> 00:08:16.397
I think you can appreciate
why I wanted to tell you about it.

93
00:08:16.941 --> 00:08:19.432
I certainly can.

94
00:08:19.944 --> 00:08:22.504
I also understand
why your people in Denver...

95
00:08:22.714 --> 00:08:24.978
...left it for you to tell me.

96
00:08:26.184 --> 00:08:28.880
Obviously. some people
can be put off...

97
00:08:29.087 --> 00:08:33.183
...from staying in a place where
something like that happened.

98
00:08:33.391 --> 00:08:38.294
You can rest assured that's not
going to happen with me.

99
00:08:38.496 --> 00:08:42.159
And as far as my wife
is concerned...

100
00:08:42.367 --> 00:08:46.201
...I'm sure she'll be absolutely
fascinated when I tell her.

101
00:08:46.404 --> 00:08:49.237
She's a confirmed ghost story...

102
00:08:49.441 --> 00:08:51.875
...and horror film addict.

103
00:08:56.714 --> 00:09:00.411
Tony. do you think
Dad'll get the job?

104
00:09:01.820 --> 00:09:04.015
He already did.

105
00:09:04.456 --> 00:09:08.187
He's going to phone Wendy up
in a few minutes to tell her.

106
00:09:22.907 --> 00:09:25.569
- Hi. babe.
- Hi. hon. How's it going?

107
00:09:25.777 --> 00:09:29.372
Great. I'm at the hotel and
I still have a lot to go through.

108
00:09:29.581 --> 00:09:32.709
I don't think I can get home
before 9:00 or 10:00.

109
00:09:32.917 --> 00:09:34.407
Sounds like you got the job.

110
00:09:34.619 --> 00:09:37.315
Right. It's a beautiful place.

111
00:09:37.522 --> 00:09:39.649
You and Danny are going to love it.

112
00:09:41.126 --> 00:09:44.027
Tony. why don't you want to go
to the hotel?

113
00:09:44.295 --> 00:09:46.024
I don't know.

114
00:09:47.098 --> 00:09:50.625
You do too know.
Now come on. tell me.

115
00:09:51.202 --> 00:09:53.261
I don't want to.

116
00:09:53.972 --> 00:09:55.234
Please.

117
00:09:56.474 --> 00:09:57.600
No.

118
00:09:57.909 --> 00:10:00.002
Now. Tony. tell me.

119
00:10:57.168 --> 00:11:01.332
We must really be high up.
The air feels so different.

120
00:11:06.978 --> 00:11:08.206
Dad?

121
00:11:11.015 --> 00:11:12.710
I'm hungry.

122
00:11:14.552 --> 00:11:17.282
You should've eaten your breakfast.

123
00:11:18.122 --> 00:11:21.023
We'll get you something
as soon as we get to the hotel.

124
00:11:21.226 --> 00:11:22.853
Okay. Mom.

125
00:11:24.295 --> 00:11:28.425
Wasn't it around here that
the Donner party got snowbound?

126
00:11:30.168 --> 00:11:33.660
I think that was farther west.
in the Sierras.

127
00:11:35.139 --> 00:11:37.573
What was the Donner party?

128
00:11:39.510 --> 00:11:43.776
They were a party of settlers
in covered wagon times.

129
00:11:44.015 --> 00:11:47.280
They got snowbound one winter
in the mountains.

130
00:11:47.485 --> 00:11:51.683
They had to resort to cannibalism
in order to stay alive.

131
00:11:52.824 --> 00:11:55.725
You mean they ate each other up?

132
00:11:55.927 --> 00:11:59.021
They had to in order to survive.

133
00:11:59.230 --> 00:12:00.458
Jack.

134
00:12:00.665 --> 00:12:01.757
Don't worry. Mom.

135
00:12:01.966 --> 00:12:06.300
I know all about cannibalism.
I saw it on TV.

136
00:12:06.504 --> 00:12:09.132
See. it's okay.

137
00:12:09.340 --> 00:12:11.774
He saw it all on the television.

138
00:12:42.473 --> 00:12:44.304
- What time does the plane leave?
- 8:30.

139
00:12:44.509 --> 00:12:47.273
That gives us plenty of time
to go over everything.

140
00:12:47.478 --> 00:12:49.412
- Goodbye. Mr. Ullman.
- Bye.

141
00:12:49.614 --> 00:12:52.742
Good morning. I hope you
haven't been waiting too long.

142
00:12:52.950 --> 00:12:55.578
No problem. We had time
to grab a bite to eat.

143
00:12:55.787 --> 00:12:58.688
Good. Glad you made it
before they shut down the kitchen.

144
00:12:58.890 --> 00:13:00.619
Is your family
having a look around?

145
00:13:00.825 --> 00:13:04.192
No. my son's
discovered the games room.

146
00:13:04.395 --> 00:13:07.489
- Has your luggage been brought in?
- Right there.

147
00:13:08.066 --> 00:13:10.034
In view of all we have
to cover today...

148
00:13:10.234 --> 00:13:13.897
...I suggest we have a quick look
at your apartment and get started.

149
00:13:14.105 --> 00:13:16.869
Have the Torrances' things
brought to their apartment.

150
00:13:17.075 --> 00:13:19.771
I'd better collect my family first.

151
00:13:27.919 --> 00:13:30.285
This is our Colorado Lounge.

152
00:13:30.488 --> 00:13:32.922
It's beautiful.

153
00:13:33.324 --> 00:13:35.189
My God!

154
00:13:35.393 --> 00:13:37.953
This place is fantastic.
isn't it. hon?

155
00:13:38.162 --> 00:13:39.493
It sure is.

156
00:14:32.417 --> 00:14:34.977
This is the staff wing
of the hotel.

157
00:14:35.953 --> 00:14:39.286
None of the other bedrooms
are heated during the winter.

158
00:14:39.524 --> 00:14:42.425
- Goodbye. Mr. Ullman.
- Goodbye. girls.

159
00:14:42.660 --> 00:14:44.651
And here are your quarters.

160
00:14:45.062 --> 00:14:47.656
Living room. bedroom. bathroom.

161
00:14:47.865 --> 00:14:50.356
And a small bedroom for your son.

162
00:14:53.971 --> 00:14:55.996
Perfect for a child.

163
00:15:04.549 --> 00:15:06.642
When was the Overlook built?

164
00:15:07.652 --> 00:15:09.882
Construction started in 1 907.

165
00:15:10.087 --> 00:15:12.055
It was finished in 1 909.

166
00:15:12.256 --> 00:15:14.918
The site's supposed to be
on an Indian burial ground.

167
00:15:15.126 --> 00:15:16.753
They actually had to repel...

168
00:15:16.961 --> 00:15:19.862
...a few Indian attacks as they
were building it.

169
00:15:20.465 --> 00:15:22.365
That's our Snowcat.

170
00:15:23.067 --> 00:15:25.092
Can you both drive a car?

171
00:15:25.636 --> 00:15:29.197
That's fine. Basically the Snowcat
operates very much like a car.

172
00:15:29.407 --> 00:15:31.136
You'll get the hang of it.

173
00:15:31.909 --> 00:15:33.536
This is the kitchen. huh?

174
00:15:33.744 --> 00:15:35.336
This is it.

175
00:15:35.546 --> 00:15:38.481
How do you like it. Danny?
Is it big enough for you?

176
00:15:39.317 --> 00:15:41.512
It's the biggest place I ever seen.

177
00:15:41.752 --> 00:15:44.084
This whole place
is such an enormous maze.

178
00:15:44.288 --> 00:15:47.849
I'll have to leave a trail of
breadcrumbs every time I come in.

179
00:15:48.759 --> 00:15:50.624
Don't let it get you down.

180
00:15:50.828 --> 00:15:53.319
It's big. but it ain't
nothing but a kitchen.

181
00:15:53.531 --> 00:15:55.726
A lot of this stuff
you'll never have to touch.

182
00:15:55.933 --> 00:15:58.163
I wouldn't know
what to do with it if I did.

183
00:15:58.369 --> 00:16:01.497
One thing for sure. you don't
have to worry about food.

184
00:16:01.706 --> 00:16:06.370
You folks could eat here for a year
and never have the same menu twice.

185
00:16:06.577 --> 00:16:09.671
Right here is
our walk-in freezer.

186
00:16:10.815 --> 00:16:13.875
This is where we keep
all of our meat.

187
00:16:14.085 --> 00:16:16.076
You got 1 5 rib roasts...

188
00:16:16.287 --> 00:16:18.414
...30 ten-pound bags of hamburger.

189
00:16:18.623 --> 00:16:21.683
We got 1 2 turkeys.
about 40 chickens...

190
00:16:21.893 --> 00:16:24.987
...50 sirloin steaks.
two dozen of pork roast...

191
00:16:25.196 --> 00:16:28.165
...and 20 legs of lamb.
Do you like lamb. Doc?

192
00:16:29.400 --> 00:16:31.766
You don't?
What's your favorite food. then?

193
00:16:31.969 --> 00:16:33.834
French fries and ketchup.

194
00:16:34.572 --> 00:16:36.563
I think we can
manage that too. Doc.

195
00:16:36.774 --> 00:16:38.503
Come along. now.
Watch your step.

196
00:16:45.249 --> 00:16:46.807
How'd you know we call him Doc?

197
00:16:47.018 --> 00:16:51.045
- Beg your pardon?
- Doc. You called Danny "Doc" twice.

198
00:16:51.255 --> 00:16:52.654
I did?

199
00:16:53.457 --> 00:16:56.585
We call him Doc sometimes.
like in the Bugs Bunny cartoons.

200
00:16:56.794 --> 00:16:58.056
But how did you know?

201
00:16:58.262 --> 00:17:00.787
I guess I probably
heard you call him that.

202
00:17:00.998 --> 00:17:03.262
It's possible.
But I honestly don't remember...

203
00:17:03.467 --> 00:17:05.662
...calling him that
since we've been with you.

204
00:17:05.870 --> 00:17:08.065
Anyway. he looks
like a Doc. doesn't he?

205
00:17:09.507 --> 00:17:10.940
What's up. Doc?

206
00:17:12.777 --> 00:17:14.972
Now. this is the storeroom.

207
00:17:16.714 --> 00:17:18.545
In here is where we keep...

208
00:17:18.749 --> 00:17:21.547
...all the dried goods
and the canned goods.

209
00:17:21.752 --> 00:17:24.186
We got canned fruits
and vegetables...

210
00:17:24.388 --> 00:17:28.188
...canned fish and meats.
hot and cold cereals.

211
00:17:28.392 --> 00:17:31.589
Post Toasties. Corn Flakes.
Sugar Puffs...

212
00:17:31.796 --> 00:17:35.823
...Rice Krispies. oatmeal.
Wheatena and Cream of Wheat.

213
00:17:36.067 --> 00:17:38.501
You got a dozen jugs
of black molasses.

214
00:17:38.703 --> 00:17:41.900
We got 60 boxes of dried milk...

215
00:17:49.547 --> 00:17:52.015
How'd you like some ice cream. Doc?

216
00:17:54.418 --> 00:17:56.409
Sociables. finger rolls...

217
00:17:56.621 --> 00:17:58.145
...and 7 kinds of what have you.

218
00:17:58.356 --> 00:18:01.883
Now. we've got dried peaches.
dried apricots...

219
00:18:02.093 --> 00:18:05.187
...dried raisins and dried prunes.

220
00:18:05.396 --> 00:18:09.696
You know. you got to keep regular
if you want to be happy.

221
00:18:12.603 --> 00:18:14.230
- How're you getting on?
- Fine.

222
00:18:14.438 --> 00:18:17.999
Can we borrow Mrs. Torrance?
We're on our way to the basement.

223
00:18:18.209 --> 00:18:20.143
I promise we won't
keep her very long.

224
00:18:20.344 --> 00:18:23.541
No problem. Mr. Ullman. I was just
getting to the ice cream.

225
00:18:23.748 --> 00:18:25.613
You like ice cream. Doc?

226
00:18:26.484 --> 00:18:27.451
I thought you did.

227
00:18:27.652 --> 00:18:30.712
You folks mind if I give Danny
some ice cream while we wait?

228
00:18:30.921 --> 00:18:32.752
- Not at all.
- We don't mind.

229
00:18:32.957 --> 00:18:35.152
- Good.
- Sound good to you. Doc?

230
00:18:35.359 --> 00:18:37.418
Okay. you behave yourself.

231
00:18:40.431 --> 00:18:42.296
What kind of ice cream
do you like?

232
00:18:42.500 --> 00:18:43.398
Chocolate.

233
00:18:43.601 --> 00:18:46.570
Chocolate it shall be.
Come on. son.

234
00:18:51.142 --> 00:18:53.133
It's amazing. all this
activity today.

235
00:18:53.344 --> 00:18:56.142
The guests and some staff
left yesterday. but the...

236
00:18:56.347 --> 00:18:57.780
...last day's always hectic.

237
00:18:57.982 --> 00:19:01.042
Everybody wants to be on their way
as early as possible.

238
00:19:01.252 --> 00:19:05.279
By 5:00 tonight. you'll never
know anybody was ever here.

239
00:19:05.489 --> 00:19:07.548
Just like a ghost ship. huh?

240
00:19:13.230 --> 00:19:16.199
Do you know how I knew
your name was Doc?

241
00:19:22.773 --> 00:19:25.173
You know what I'm
talking about. don't you?

242
00:19:32.149 --> 00:19:35.641
I can remember when I was
a little boy...

243
00:19:36.053 --> 00:19:38.578
...my grandmother and I
could hold conversations...

244
00:19:38.789 --> 00:19:42.623
...entirely without ever
opening our mouths.

245
00:19:43.694 --> 00:19:45.992
She called it "shining."

246
00:19:47.498 --> 00:19:50.228
And for a long time I thought
it was just the two of us...

247
00:19:50.434 --> 00:19:52.959
...that had "the shine" to us.

248
00:19:53.671 --> 00:19:56.663
Just like you probably thought
you was the only one.

249
00:19:57.341 --> 00:19:59.206
But there are other folks...

250
00:19:59.410 --> 00:20:03.141
...though mostly they don't
know it. or don't believe it.

251
00:20:07.818 --> 00:20:10.252
How long have you
been able to do it?

252
00:20:15.459 --> 00:20:17.859
Why don't you want
to talk about it?

253
00:20:23.100 --> 00:20:25.159
I'm not supposed to.

254
00:20:26.737 --> 00:20:29.262
Who says you ain't supposed to?

255
00:20:32.710 --> 00:20:34.109
Tony.

256
00:20:36.080 --> 00:20:37.741
Who's Tony?

257
00:20:40.217 --> 00:20:43.618
Tony's the little boy
that lives in my mouth.

258
00:20:45.556 --> 00:20:47.581
Is Tony the one
that...

259
00:20:47.792 --> 00:20:49.350
...tells you things?

260
00:20:53.898 --> 00:20:56.264
How does he tell you things?

261
00:20:58.102 --> 00:21:02.402
It's like I go to sleep.
and he shows me things.

262
00:21:02.606 --> 00:21:06.702
But when I wake up.
I can't remember everything.

263
00:21:08.546 --> 00:21:12.243
Does your mom and dad
know about Tony?

264
00:21:15.553 --> 00:21:18.113
Do they know he tells you things?

265
00:21:18.989 --> 00:21:21.924
Tony told me never to tell them.

266
00:21:24.061 --> 00:21:27.428
Has Tony ever told you
anything about this place?

267
00:21:27.631 --> 00:21:30.191
About the Overlook Hotel?

268
00:21:33.470 --> 00:21:35.028
I don't know.

269
00:21:35.940 --> 00:21:39.967
Now think real hard. Doc. Think.

270
00:21:45.249 --> 00:21:47.649
Is there something bad here?

271
00:21:59.263 --> 00:22:01.697
You know. Doc.
when something happens...

272
00:22:01.899 --> 00:22:05.528
...it can leave a trace
of itself behind.

273
00:22:06.303 --> 00:22:07.861
Say. like...

274
00:22:08.072 --> 00:22:11.132
...if someone burns toast.

275
00:22:13.244 --> 00:22:17.908
Maybe things that happen
leave other kind of traces behind.

276
00:22:19.083 --> 00:22:22.519
Not things that anyone
can notice.

277
00:22:22.720 --> 00:22:27.521
But things that people
who shine can see.

278
00:22:28.626 --> 00:22:31.925
Just like they can see things
that haven't happened yet...

279
00:22:34.198 --> 00:22:38.362
...sometimes they can see things
that happened a long time ago.

280
00:22:39.904 --> 00:22:42.771
I think a lot of things
happened right here...

281
00:22:42.973 --> 00:22:46.670
...in this particular hotel
over the years.

282
00:22:47.211 --> 00:22:49.611
And not all of them
was good.

283
00:22:52.917 --> 00:22:55.545
What about room 237?

284
00:22:58.889 --> 00:23:01.084
Room 237?

285
00:23:02.393 --> 00:23:05.487
You're scared of room 237.
ain't you?

286
00:23:07.264 --> 00:23:08.731
No. I ain't.

287
00:23:10.234 --> 00:23:14.068
Mr. Hallorann. what is in room 237?

288
00:23:15.406 --> 00:23:16.771
Nothing.

289
00:23:17.207 --> 00:23:20.438
There ain't nothing in room 237.

290
00:23:20.644 --> 00:23:23.875
But you ain't got no business
going in there anyway.

291
00:23:24.081 --> 00:23:26.208
So stay out.

292
00:23:26.417 --> 00:23:28.908
You understand? Stay out!

293
00:24:45.162 --> 00:24:46.891
Good morning. hon.

294
00:24:48.899 --> 00:24:50.662
Your breakfast is ready.

295
00:24:51.435 --> 00:24:53.062
What time is it?

296
00:24:53.270 --> 00:24:55.135
It's about 1 1:30.

297
00:24:57.041 --> 00:24:58.633
Jesus.

298
00:24:59.576 --> 00:25:02.010
I guess we've been
staying up too late.

299
00:25:02.312 --> 00:25:03.745
I know it.

300
00:25:05.049 --> 00:25:07.916
I made them just the way
you like them. sunny-side up.

301
00:25:08.218 --> 00:25:09.776
Nice.

302
00:25:12.056 --> 00:25:13.853
It's really pretty outside.

303
00:25:14.058 --> 00:25:17.289
How about taking me for a walk
after you finish your breakfast?

304
00:25:17.895 --> 00:25:22.229
I suppose I ought to try
to do some writing first.

305
00:25:23.667 --> 00:25:25.328
Any ideas yet?

306
00:25:26.336 --> 00:25:27.997
Lots of ideas.

307
00:25:28.205 --> 00:25:29.729
No good ones.

308
00:25:30.207 --> 00:25:32.675
Something will come.

309
00:25:33.177 --> 00:25:37.113
It's just a matter of settling into
the habit of writing every day.

310
00:25:38.682 --> 00:25:40.377
That's all it is.

311
00:25:59.736 --> 00:26:02.296
- All right.
- And you're going to lose.

312
00:26:02.506 --> 00:26:05.634
And I'm going to get you.
You'd better run fast!

313
00:26:10.647 --> 00:26:11.773
Look out!

314
00:26:11.982 --> 00:26:13.847
I'm coming in close.

315
00:26:14.051 --> 00:26:16.542
Loser has to keep America clean.

316
00:26:16.787 --> 00:26:18.414
Keep America clean.

317
00:26:19.423 --> 00:26:20.890
Danny. you win.

318
00:26:21.225 --> 00:26:23.557
Let's take the rest
of this walking.

319
00:26:26.096 --> 00:26:27.495
Give me your hand.

320
00:26:30.134 --> 00:26:31.931
Isn't it beautiful?

321
00:26:49.686 --> 00:26:51.051
Dead end.

322
00:27:48.512 --> 00:27:50.139
We made it.

323
00:27:50.647 --> 00:27:51.875
Isn't it beautiful?

324
00:28:13.570 --> 00:28:15.401
It's so pretty.

325
00:28:19.977 --> 00:28:22.946
I didn't think it was
going to be this big. Did you?

326
00:31:00.937 --> 00:31:02.370
Hi. hon.

327
00:31:05.976 --> 00:31:07.375
How's it going?

328
00:31:09.946 --> 00:31:11.106
Fine.

329
00:31:13.216 --> 00:31:14.774
Get a lot written today?

330
00:31:21.825 --> 00:31:24.385
The weather forecast
said it's going to snow tonight.

331
00:31:29.599 --> 00:31:31.931
What do you want me
to do about it?

332
00:31:34.070 --> 00:31:36.231
Come on. hon.

333
00:31:36.573 --> 00:31:38.598
Don't be so grouchy.

334
00:31:39.009 --> 00:31:40.340
I'm not...

335
00:31:40.710 --> 00:31:41.904
...being grouchy.

336
00:31:42.112 --> 00:31:44.910
I just want to finish my work.

337
00:31:48.418 --> 00:31:50.818
Okay. I understand.

338
00:31:51.054 --> 00:31:53.648
I'll come back later
with a couple of sandwiches.

339
00:31:53.857 --> 00:31:56.325
Maybe you'll let me
read something then.

340
00:31:59.529 --> 00:32:00.621
Wendy...

341
00:32:00.831 --> 00:32:03.425
...let me explain something to you.

342
00:32:04.334 --> 00:32:08.202
When you come in and interrupt.
you're breaking my concentration.

343
00:32:08.405 --> 00:32:09.838
You're distracting me...

344
00:32:10.040 --> 00:32:13.476
...and it will then take me time
to get back to where I was.

345
00:32:13.677 --> 00:32:15.110
Understand?

346
00:32:18.582 --> 00:32:19.742
Fine.

347
00:32:20.917 --> 00:32:22.646
We're going to make a new rule:

348
00:32:22.853 --> 00:32:24.286
Whenever I'm in here...

349
00:32:24.488 --> 00:32:26.752
...and you hear me typing...

350
00:32:28.558 --> 00:32:31.493
...or whatever the fuck
you hear me doing in here...

351
00:32:31.695 --> 00:32:33.993
...when I'm in here.
that means I am working.

352
00:32:34.197 --> 00:32:36.427
That means don't come in.

353
00:32:36.633 --> 00:32:38.897
Now. do you think
you can handle that?

354
00:32:43.540 --> 00:32:44.666
Fine.

355
00:32:45.709 --> 00:32:49.008
Why don't you start right now
and get the fuck out of here?

356
00:33:14.371 --> 00:33:15.429
Missed!

357
00:33:21.011 --> 00:33:21.841
Don't have!

358
00:33:22.078 --> 00:33:23.807
No fair anymore.

359
00:34:31.247 --> 00:34:32.544
I knew it.

360
00:35:02.812 --> 00:35:06.304
This is IKDIK 1 2 calling IKDIK 1.

361
00:35:08.818 --> 00:35:12.515
KDK 1 2 to KDK 1.

362
00:35:12.722 --> 00:35:15.850
This is IKDIK 1.
We're receiving you. Over.

363
00:35:16.226 --> 00:35:19.354
Hi. this is Wendy Torrance
at the Overlook Hotel.

364
00:35:19.929 --> 00:35:22.727
Hi. how are you folks
getting on up there? Over.

365
00:35:22.999 --> 00:35:24.330
We're just fine.

366
00:35:24.534 --> 00:35:27.002
But our telephones
aren't doing too well.

367
00:35:27.203 --> 00:35:30.229
Are the lines down.
by any chance? Over.

368
00:35:30.874 --> 00:35:34.674
Yes. quite a few of them are down
due to the storm. Over.

369
00:35:34.978 --> 00:35:38.175
Any chance of them
being repaired soon? Over.

370
00:35:38.381 --> 00:35:39.541
Well. I wouldn't like to say.

371
00:35:39.749 --> 00:35:43.185
Most winters they stay that way
until spring. Over.

372
00:35:43.687 --> 00:35:47.088
Boy. this storm is really something.
isn't it? Over.

373
00:35:47.557 --> 00:35:50.458
Yes. It's one of the worst we've
had for years.

374
00:35:51.027 --> 00:35:54.224
Is there anything else we can
do for you. Mrs. Torrance?

375
00:35:54.698 --> 00:35:56.859
I suppose not. Over.

376
00:35:57.467 --> 00:36:00.766
If you folks have any problems
up there. just give us a call.

377
00:36:00.970 --> 00:36:02.267
And. Mrs. Torrance?

378
00:36:02.472 --> 00:36:06.670
It might be a good idea if you
leave your radio on all the time.

379
00:36:07.510 --> 00:36:09.000
Okay. We'll do that.

380
00:36:09.212 --> 00:36:11.271
It was real nice talking to you.

381
00:36:11.481 --> 00:36:14.109
Bye. Over and out.

382
00:36:49.018 --> 00:36:51.213
Hello. Danny.

383
00:36:56.493 --> 00:36:58.927
Come and play with us.

384
00:37:03.800 --> 00:37:06.564
Come and play with us. Danny.

385
00:37:08.404 --> 00:37:10.269
Forever...

386
00:37:12.041 --> 00:37:13.804
...and ever...

387
00:37:14.744 --> 00:37:16.769
...and ever.

388
00:37:48.244 --> 00:37:49.871
Tony...

389
00:37:50.880 --> 00:37:52.905
...I'm scared.

390
00:37:58.388 --> 00:38:01.949
Remember what Mr. Hallorann said.

391
00:38:03.560 --> 00:38:07.462
It's just like
pictures in a book. Danny.

392
00:38:07.664 --> 00:38:09.825
It isn't real.

393
00:39:04.275 --> 00:39:07.438
Can I go to my room
and get my fire engine?

394
00:39:11.182 --> 00:39:13.377
Come here for a minute first.

395
00:39:50.388 --> 00:39:52.185
How's it going. Doc?

396
00:39:56.761 --> 00:39:58.558
Having a good time?

397
00:40:00.632 --> 00:40:02.099
Yes. Dad.

398
00:40:05.003 --> 00:40:06.231
Good.

399
00:40:08.439 --> 00:40:10.600
I want you to
have a good time.

400
00:40:11.309 --> 00:40:12.936
I am. Dad.

401
00:40:23.388 --> 00:40:25.185
Do you feel bad?

402
00:40:31.129 --> 00:40:33.427
I'm just a little bit tired.

403
00:40:34.999 --> 00:40:37.559
Then why don't you
go to sleep?

404
00:40:41.139 --> 00:40:42.697
I can't.

405
00:40:44.175 --> 00:40:46.473
I got too much to do.

406
00:40:55.787 --> 00:40:58.051
Do you like this hotel?

407
00:41:04.062 --> 00:41:05.461
I do.

408
00:41:06.431 --> 00:41:07.762
I love it.

409
00:41:09.967 --> 00:41:11.298
Don't you?

410
00:41:13.671 --> 00:41:15.161
I guess so.

411
00:41:17.809 --> 00:41:19.003
Good.

412
00:41:22.213 --> 00:41:24.545
I want you to like it here.

413
00:41:28.519 --> 00:41:31.920
I wish we could stay here
forever...

414
00:41:32.123 --> 00:41:33.920
...and ever...

415
00:41:34.592 --> 00:41:35.923
...and ever.

416
00:41:41.365 --> 00:41:42.389
What?

417
00:41:43.668 --> 00:41:46.762
You would never hurt Mommy or me.
would you?

418
00:41:52.243 --> 00:41:53.733
What do you mean?

419
00:41:58.850 --> 00:42:01.444
Did your mother ever
say that to you?

420
00:42:02.120 --> 00:42:03.917
That I would hurt you?

421
00:42:04.689 --> 00:42:06.054
No. Dad.

422
00:42:08.226 --> 00:42:09.784
You sure?

423
00:42:10.328 --> 00:42:11.886
Yes. Dad.

424
00:42:16.701 --> 00:42:18.726
I love you. Danny.

425
00:42:19.937 --> 00:42:22.531
I love you
more than anything else...

426
00:42:22.740 --> 00:42:25.300
...in the whole world...

427
00:42:26.077 --> 00:42:29.137
...and I would never do anything
to hurt you...

428
00:42:29.447 --> 00:42:30.675
...never.

429
00:42:31.549 --> 00:42:33.608
You know that. don't you?

430
00:42:34.085 --> 00:42:35.643
Yes. Dad.

431
00:42:36.587 --> 00:42:37.679
Good.

432
00:44:05.610 --> 00:44:07.373
Mom. are you in there?

433
00:45:26.624 --> 00:45:27.682
What happened?

434
00:45:27.892 --> 00:45:29.120
Honey...

435
00:45:29.994 --> 00:45:31.393
...what's wrong?

436
00:45:39.570 --> 00:45:40.969
I had the most...

437
00:45:41.172 --> 00:45:43.766
...terrible nightmare I ever had.

438
00:45:45.710 --> 00:45:48.645
- It was the most horrible dream.
- It's okay. it's okay now.

439
00:45:49.847 --> 00:45:51.212
Really.

440
00:45:55.486 --> 00:45:57.078
I dreamed that I...

441
00:45:57.288 --> 00:45:59.722
...that I killed
you and Danny.

442
00:46:02.460 --> 00:46:04.690
But I didn't just kill you.

443
00:46:05.997 --> 00:46:08.761
I cut you up
into little pieces.

444
00:46:11.435 --> 00:46:12.959
My God.

445
00:46:13.671 --> 00:46:16.231
I must be losing my mind.

446
00:46:18.509 --> 00:46:21.137
Everything's going to be
all right.

447
00:46:23.247 --> 00:46:25.943
Come on. Let's get up
off the floor.

448
00:46:33.791 --> 00:46:36.089
There. Now sit up.

449
00:46:36.727 --> 00:46:38.024
It's okay.

450
00:46:39.130 --> 00:46:40.563
It's okay.

451
00:46:44.635 --> 00:46:45.829
Danny!

452
00:46:46.137 --> 00:46:48.071
Everything's okay!

453
00:46:48.272 --> 00:46:51.435
Just go play in your room
for a while.

454
00:46:51.776 --> 00:46:53.835
Your dad's just got
a headache.

455
00:46:55.146 --> 00:46:58.172
Danny. mind what I say.
Go play in your room.

456
00:47:00.151 --> 00:47:03.086
Honey. let me just go
get him out of here.

457
00:47:03.287 --> 00:47:04.811
I'll be right back.

458
00:47:06.724 --> 00:47:08.783
Why don't you mind me?

459
00:47:15.399 --> 00:47:17.230
Oh. my God.

460
00:47:18.436 --> 00:47:20.836
What happened to your neck?

461
00:47:22.773 --> 00:47:24.900
What happened to your neck?

462
00:47:53.871 --> 00:47:55.839
You did this to him...

463
00:47:56.273 --> 00:47:57.706
...didn't you?!

464
00:47:59.543 --> 00:48:01.602
You son of a bitch!

465
00:48:01.812 --> 00:48:03.677
You did this to him!

466
00:48:03.881 --> 00:48:05.314
Didn't you?!

467
00:48:06.650 --> 00:48:08.311
How could you?!

468
00:48:08.552 --> 00:48:10.281
How could you?!

469
00:49:40.144 --> 00:49:43.238
God! I'd give anything
for a drink.

470
00:49:45.883 --> 00:49:48.784
I'd give my goddamn soul...

471
00:49:48.986 --> 00:49:51.477
...for just a glass of beer.

472
00:50:06.470 --> 00:50:07.960
Hi. Lloyd.

473
00:50:11.508 --> 00:50:13.908
A little slow tonight.
isn't it?

474
00:50:18.782 --> 00:50:21.046
Yes it is. Mr. Torrance.

475
00:50:23.120 --> 00:50:24.587
What will it be?

476
00:50:26.257 --> 00:50:29.226
I'm awfully glad
you asked me that. Lloyd...

477
00:50:29.426 --> 00:50:32.759
...because I just happen to have
two twenties...

478
00:50:32.963 --> 00:50:35.864
...and two tens
right here in my wallet.

479
00:50:36.066 --> 00:50:39.331
I was afraid they were
going to be there until next April.

480
00:50:40.037 --> 00:50:41.868
So here's what:

481
00:50:42.172 --> 00:50:44.470
You slip me a bottle of bourbon...

482
00:50:44.675 --> 00:50:47.473
...a little glass and some ice.

483
00:50:47.678 --> 00:50:49.703
You can do that.
can't you. Lloyd?

484
00:50:50.147 --> 00:50:52.513
You're not too busy. are you?

485
00:50:53.083 --> 00:50:55.574
No. sir.
I'm not busy at all.

486
00:50:56.086 --> 00:50:57.644
Good man.

487
00:50:57.955 --> 00:50:59.047
You set them up...

488
00:50:59.323 --> 00:51:02.190
...and I'll knock them back.
one by one.

489
00:51:03.327 --> 00:51:06.262
White man's burden.
Lloyd. my man.

490
00:51:06.463 --> 00:51:08.624
White man's burden.

491
00:51:14.705 --> 00:51:15.831
Say. Lloyd...

492
00:51:16.040 --> 00:51:18.804
...it seems I'm temporarily light.

493
00:51:19.143 --> 00:51:21.577
How's my credit
in this joint. anyway?

494
00:51:21.845 --> 00:51:24.211
Your credit's fine. Mr. Torrance.

495
00:51:24.915 --> 00:51:26.542
That's swell.

496
00:51:26.750 --> 00:51:28.445
I like you. Lloyd.

497
00:51:28.652 --> 00:51:30.313
I always liked you.

498
00:51:30.521 --> 00:51:32.853
You were always the best of them.

499
00:51:33.057 --> 00:51:35.423
Best goddamned bartender...

500
00:51:35.626 --> 00:51:38.561
...from Timbuktu
to Portland. Maine.

501
00:51:38.762 --> 00:51:40.992
Or Portland. Oregon.
for that matter.

502
00:51:41.265 --> 00:51:43.062
Thank you for saying so.

503
00:51:55.546 --> 00:51:58.777
I never laid a hand on him.
goddamn it.

504
00:51:58.982 --> 00:52:00.609
I didn't.

505
00:52:02.653 --> 00:52:07.249
I wouldn't touch one hair
on his goddamn little head.

506
00:52:07.858 --> 00:52:10.986
I love the little
son of a bitch.

507
00:52:12.596 --> 00:52:15.429
I'd do anything for him.

508
00:52:15.632 --> 00:52:18.430
Any fucking thing for him.

509
00:52:22.506 --> 00:52:25.066
But that bitch!

510
00:52:26.076 --> 00:52:27.771
As long as I live...

511
00:52:28.045 --> 00:52:31.446
...she'll never let me forget
what happened.

512
00:52:41.058 --> 00:52:43.891
I did hurt him once. okay?

513
00:52:44.261 --> 00:52:46.320
It was an accident.

514
00:52:46.630 --> 00:52:49.224
Completely unintentional.

515
00:52:50.501 --> 00:52:52.731
It could have happened
to anybody.

516
00:52:54.471 --> 00:52:57.929
And it was three goddamn
years ago!

517
00:52:58.142 --> 00:53:00.975
The little fucker had thrown all my
papers all over the floor.

518
00:53:01.178 --> 00:53:03.646
All I tried to do was pull him up.

519
00:53:06.417 --> 00:53:11.116
A momentary loss of
muscular coordination.

520
00:53:11.422 --> 00:53:12.650
I mean...

521
00:53:13.190 --> 00:53:16.717
...a few extra foot-pounds
of energy...

522
00:53:16.927 --> 00:53:19.760
...per second. per second.

523
00:53:35.879 --> 00:53:37.779
Thank God you're here.

524
00:53:41.018 --> 00:53:43.213
There's someone else
in the hotel with us.

525
00:53:43.420 --> 00:53:45.945
There's a crazy woman
in one of the rooms.

526
00:53:46.156 --> 00:53:48.716
She tried to strangle Danny.

527
00:53:51.261 --> 00:53:53.661
Are you out of your fucking mind?

528
00:53:55.599 --> 00:53:57.624
It's the truth! Really.

529
00:53:57.835 --> 00:53:59.826
I swear it.
Danny told me.

530
00:54:00.170 --> 00:54:02.035
He went up into
one of the bedrooms.

531
00:54:02.239 --> 00:54:05.697
The door was open. and he saw this
crazy woman in the bathtub.

532
00:54:05.909 --> 00:54:08.241
She tried to strangle him!

533
00:54:11.949 --> 00:54:13.712
Which room was it?

534
00:54:21.358 --> 00:54:23.485
From Channel 10 in Miami...

535
00:54:23.694 --> 00:54:26.060
...this is Newswatch
with Glen Rinker...

536
00:54:26.263 --> 00:54:30.461
...Ann Bishop. and
the award-winning Newswatch team.

537
00:54:30.801 --> 00:54:33.235
Good evening. I'm Glen Rinker.
Newswatch Ten.

538
00:54:33.437 --> 00:54:36.565
As Miami continues to swelter
in a record winter heat wave...

539
00:54:36.773 --> 00:54:38.900
...bringing temperatures
to the 90s...

540
00:54:39.109 --> 00:54:42.237
...Central and Mountain states
are buried in snow.

541
00:54:42.446 --> 00:54:46.439
In Colorado. 10 inches of snow
fell in just a few hours tonight.

542
00:54:46.650 --> 00:54:48.880
Travel in the Rockies
is almost impossible.

543
00:54:49.086 --> 00:54:52.055
Airports are shut down. stranding
thousands of passengers.

544
00:54:52.256 --> 00:54:54.156
Highways are blocked
by snowdrifts.

545
00:54:54.358 --> 00:54:56.121
Railroad tracks are frozen.

546
00:54:56.326 --> 00:54:58.351
Officials in Colorado
tell Newswatch...

547
00:54:58.562 --> 00:55:02.123
...at least 3 have been killed
by exposure to freezing winds.

548
00:55:02.332 --> 00:55:04.630
The governor of Colorado
is expected...

549
00:55:04.835 --> 00:55:06.564
...to declare
a weather emergency.

550
00:55:06.770 --> 00:55:08.601
The National Guard
might be called out...

551
00:55:08.805 --> 00:55:09.999
...to clear streets and roads.

552
00:55:10.207 --> 00:55:12.437
Weather forecasters
predict more snow...

553
00:55:12.643 --> 00:55:14.634
...and heavy winds
tonight and tomorrow...

554
00:55:14.845 --> 00:55:17.473
...with temperatures dropping
well below zero.

555
00:55:17.681 --> 00:55:20.673
Back here in Florida.
we've got the opposite problem.

556
00:55:20.884 --> 00:55:23.114
The heat and humidity
are supposed to climb.

557
00:55:23.320 --> 00:55:25.288
Local beaches
should be jammed.

558
00:55:25.489 --> 00:55:27.514
Our weather expert.
Walter Cronice...

559
00:55:27.724 --> 00:55:30.989
...will have the local forecast
later on Newswatch.

560
01:01:02.626 --> 01:01:07.256
We're sorry. Your call cannot
be completed as dialed.

561
01:01:07.597 --> 01:01:10.725
If you need assistance.
please call the operator.

562
01:01:27.984 --> 01:01:29.815
Yes. it's me.

563
01:01:30.020 --> 01:01:31.453
Thank God.

564
01:01:36.126 --> 01:01:37.889
Did you find anything?

565
01:01:38.094 --> 01:01:40.824
No. Nothing at all.

566
01:01:41.431 --> 01:01:44.594
I didn't see one goddamn thing.

567
01:01:47.337 --> 01:01:50.829
You went into the room Danny said?
To 237?

568
01:01:51.041 --> 01:01:52.599
Yes. I did.

569
01:01:53.076 --> 01:01:54.873
And you didn't see anything at all?

570
01:01:55.078 --> 01:01:57.069
Absolutely nothing.

571
01:01:57.280 --> 01:01:58.542
How is he?

572
01:01:58.748 --> 01:02:00.545
He's still asleep.

573
01:02:00.951 --> 01:02:02.077
Good.

574
01:02:07.891 --> 01:02:10.985
I'm sure he'll be himself again
in the morning.

575
01:02:15.465 --> 01:02:17.956
Are you sure it was the right room?

576
01:02:18.168 --> 01:02:21.331
I mean. maybe Danny made a mistake.

577
01:02:21.538 --> 01:02:23.904
He must have gone in that room.

578
01:02:24.107 --> 01:02:26.769
The door was open.
the lights were on.

579
01:02:29.412 --> 01:02:31.744
I just don't understand it.

580
01:02:36.086 --> 01:02:39.112
What about those bruises
on his neck?

581
01:02:41.291 --> 01:02:43.623
Somebody did that to him.

582
01:02:51.901 --> 01:02:53.334
I think...

583
01:02:55.005 --> 01:02:57.565
...he did it to himself.

584
01:03:03.580 --> 01:03:04.808
No.

585
01:03:05.482 --> 01:03:07.507
That's not possible.

586
01:03:12.822 --> 01:03:16.485
Once you rule out his version
of what happened...

587
01:03:16.726 --> 01:03:19.320
...there is no other explanation.

588
01:03:19.796 --> 01:03:21.127
Is there?

589
01:03:27.704 --> 01:03:30.696
Whatever the explanation is...

590
01:03:34.144 --> 01:03:35.543
...I think we...

591
01:03:35.745 --> 01:03:38.475
...have to get Danny out of here.

592
01:03:43.253 --> 01:03:45.084
Get him out of here?

593
01:03:49.259 --> 01:03:50.988
You mean...

594
01:03:52.028 --> 01:03:53.996
...just leave the hotel?

595
01:04:02.972 --> 01:04:04.439
It is so...

596
01:04:04.641 --> 01:04:07.075
...typical of you to create
a problem like this...

597
01:04:07.277 --> 01:04:09.802
...when I finally have a chance
to accomplish something!

598
01:04:10.013 --> 01:04:12.573
When I'm really into my work!

599
01:04:12.782 --> 01:04:16.741
I could really write my own ticket
if I went back now. couldn't I?

600
01:04:16.953 --> 01:04:20.684
Shoveling out driveways.
work in a car wash.

601
01:04:20.890 --> 01:04:22.983
Any of that appeal to you?

602
01:04:24.194 --> 01:04:26.890
I have let you fuck up my life
so far...

603
01:04:27.097 --> 01:04:30.726
...but I am not going to let you
fuck this up.

604
01:05:42.372 --> 01:05:44.670
Good evening. Forest Service.

605
01:05:45.241 --> 01:05:46.674
My name is Dick Hallorann.

606
01:05:46.876 --> 01:05:49.310
I'm the head chef at
the Overlook Hotel.

607
01:05:49.512 --> 01:05:51.639
Good evening.
What can I do for you?

608
01:05:51.848 --> 01:05:55.409
I've been trying to make
an urgent phone call up there...

609
01:05:55.618 --> 01:05:58.917
...but the operator said
that the phone lines are down.

610
01:05:59.122 --> 01:06:02.717
A lot of lines around here
are down due to the storm.

611
01:06:02.926 --> 01:06:05.588
I hate to put you through
any trouble...

612
01:06:05.795 --> 01:06:09.026
...but there's a family up there
all by themselves with a young kid.

613
01:06:09.232 --> 01:06:10.893
And with this storm
and everything...

614
01:06:11.100 --> 01:06:14.001
...I'd appreciate it if you'd give
them a call on your radio...

615
01:06:14.204 --> 01:06:16.195
...just to see if
everything's okay.

616
01:06:16.706 --> 01:06:18.003
I'll be glad to do that.

617
01:06:18.208 --> 01:06:21.006
Why don't you call me back
in about 20 minutes?

618
01:06:21.211 --> 01:06:23.236
Thank you very much.
I'll do that.

619
01:06:23.446 --> 01:06:24.879
All right. sir.

620
01:06:45.201 --> 01:06:47.169
Good evening. Mr. Torrance.

621
01:06:47.370 --> 01:06:48.837
Good evening.

622
01:07:13.396 --> 01:07:14.863
Hi. Lloyd.

623
01:07:15.064 --> 01:07:16.929
Been away. but now I'm back.

624
01:07:17.200 --> 01:07:18.929
Good evening. Mr. Torrance.

625
01:07:19.602 --> 01:07:20.591
It's good to see you.

626
01:07:20.803 --> 01:07:23.465
It's good to be back. Lloyd.

627
01:07:24.107 --> 01:07:25.836
What'll it be. sir?

628
01:07:26.643 --> 01:07:28.907
Hair of the dog that bit me.

629
01:07:30.313 --> 01:07:31.974
Bourbon on the rocks.

630
01:07:32.815 --> 01:07:34.214
That'll do her.

631
01:07:47.730 --> 01:07:49.994
No charge to you. Mr. Torrance.

632
01:07:51.434 --> 01:07:53.402
No charge?

633
01:07:54.037 --> 01:07:56.028
Your money's no good here.

634
01:08:01.678 --> 01:08:03.407
Orders from the house.

635
01:08:06.616 --> 01:08:09.107
Orders from the house.

636
01:08:12.355 --> 01:08:14.346
Drink up. Mr. Torrance.

637
01:08:16.559 --> 01:08:21.087
I'm the kind of man likes to know
who's buying their drinks. Lloyd.

638
01:08:23.399 --> 01:08:26.334
It's not a matter that concerns you.
Mr. Torrance.

639
01:08:26.536 --> 01:08:28.470
At least. not at this point.

640
01:08:33.276 --> 01:08:35.676
Anything you say. Lloyd.

641
01:08:36.112 --> 01:08:38.103
Anything you say.

642
01:08:51.094 --> 01:08:53.562
Oh. dear! I'm so sorry. sir.

643
01:08:54.664 --> 01:08:56.131
Oh. dear. Oh. dear.

644
01:08:56.332 --> 01:08:58.892
I've made an awful mess
of your jacket. sir.

645
01:09:00.136 --> 01:09:03.765
That's all right.
I've got plenty of jackets.

646
01:09:03.973 --> 01:09:06.771
I'm afraid it's advocaat. sir.
It tends to stain.

647
01:09:06.976 --> 01:09:08.102
Advocaat. is it?

648
01:09:08.311 --> 01:09:10.472
Yes. sir.
I think the best thing...

649
01:09:10.680 --> 01:09:12.875
...is to come along
to the gentlemen's room...

650
01:09:13.082 --> 01:09:15.607
...and we'll get
some water to it. sir.

651
01:09:16.452 --> 01:09:19.751
Looks like you might have got a
spot of it on yourself...

652
01:09:19.956 --> 01:09:20.945
...Jeevesy old boy.

653
01:09:21.157 --> 01:09:24.320
That doesn't matter. sir.
You're the important one.

654
01:09:24.627 --> 01:09:27.027
Awfully nice of you to say.

655
01:09:27.463 --> 01:09:30.330
Of course. I intended to change
my jacket this evening...

656
01:09:30.533 --> 01:09:32.797
...before the fish and
goose soiree.

657
01:09:33.002 --> 01:09:35.027
Very wise. sir. Very wise.

658
01:09:35.238 --> 01:09:36.535
Here. I'll just...

659
01:09:37.507 --> 01:09:39.771
...hold this for you there.
Jeevesy.

660
01:09:39.976 --> 01:09:41.773
Thank you. sir. Thank you.

661
01:09:42.812 --> 01:09:46.441
Let's see if we can improve this
with a little water. sir.

662
01:09:46.649 --> 01:09:47.911
All right. I'll just...

663
01:09:48.117 --> 01:09:52.315
...set my bourbon and advocaat
down right there.

664
01:09:52.889 --> 01:09:54.322
Won't keep you a moment.

665
01:09:54.524 --> 01:09:55.923
Fine.

666
01:09:58.995 --> 01:10:00.656
What do they call you.
Jeevesy?

667
01:10:00.863 --> 01:10:03.423
Grady. sir. Delbert Grady.

668
01:10:08.204 --> 01:10:09.034
Grady?

669
01:10:09.238 --> 01:10:10.569
Yes. sir.

670
01:10:11.741 --> 01:10:13.072
Delbert Grady.

671
01:10:13.276 --> 01:10:14.800
That's right. sir.

672
01:10:23.519 --> 01:10:24.952
Mr. Grady...

673
01:10:25.721 --> 01:10:27.814
...haven't I seen you
somewhere before?

674
01:10:28.024 --> 01:10:30.720
Why. no. sir. I don't believe so.

675
01:10:37.767 --> 01:10:39.598
It's coming off now. sir.

676
01:10:44.540 --> 01:10:46.098
Mr. Grady...

677
01:10:47.610 --> 01:10:50.078
...weren't you once
the caretaker here?

678
01:10:50.279 --> 01:10:53.077
Why. no. sir. I don't believe so.

679
01:10:56.118 --> 01:10:59.451
You a married man. are you.
Mr. Grady?

680
01:10:59.655 --> 01:11:00.485
Yes. sir.

681
01:11:00.690 --> 01:11:03.955
I have a wife and
two daughters. sir.

682
01:11:04.994 --> 01:11:06.518
And...

683
01:11:08.197 --> 01:11:09.459
...where are they now?

684
01:11:09.665 --> 01:11:13.726
They're somewhere around.
I'm not quite sure at the moment.

685
01:11:24.413 --> 01:11:26.813
You were the caretaker here.

686
01:11:28.284 --> 01:11:30.275
I recognize you.

687
01:11:31.654 --> 01:11:34.714
I saw your picture
in the newspapers.

688
01:11:35.157 --> 01:11:36.920
You...

689
01:11:37.393 --> 01:11:40.920
...chopped your wife and daughter
up into little bits.

690
01:11:41.430 --> 01:11:42.829
And...

691
01:11:43.466 --> 01:11:45.400
...then you blew your brains out.

692
01:11:55.311 --> 01:11:57.074
That's strange. sir.

693
01:11:58.080 --> 01:12:00.810
I don't have any recollection
of that at all.

694
01:12:04.487 --> 01:12:06.352
Mr. Grady...

695
01:12:06.789 --> 01:12:10.122
...you were the caretaker here.

696
01:12:17.934 --> 01:12:20.698
I'm sorry to differ with you. sir.

697
01:12:22.572 --> 01:12:24.301
But you...

698
01:12:25.041 --> 01:12:26.872
...are the caretaker.

699
01:12:29.145 --> 01:12:32.046
You've always been the caretaker.

700
01:12:34.951 --> 01:12:36.782
I should know. sir.

701
01:12:38.220 --> 01:12:40.814
I've always been here.

702
01:12:59.041 --> 01:13:01.236
Did you know. Mr. Torrance...

703
01:13:01.477 --> 01:13:03.240
...that your son...

704
01:13:03.646 --> 01:13:06.342
...is attempting to bring
an outside party...

705
01:13:06.549 --> 01:13:08.744
...into this situation?

706
01:13:11.320 --> 01:13:13.015
Did you know that?

707
01:13:19.261 --> 01:13:21.354
He is. Mr. Torrance.

708
01:13:23.699 --> 01:13:24.859
Who?

709
01:13:27.103 --> 01:13:28.730
A nigger.

710
01:13:32.808 --> 01:13:34.207
A nigger?

711
01:13:36.946 --> 01:13:38.379
A nigger...

712
01:13:38.581 --> 01:13:39.673
...cook.

713
01:13:46.188 --> 01:13:47.450
How?

714
01:13:49.725 --> 01:13:51.488
Your son...

715
01:13:51.927 --> 01:13:54.725
...has a very great talent.

716
01:13:55.698 --> 01:13:59.190
I don't think you are aware
how great it is.

717
01:13:59.935 --> 01:14:03.166
But he is attempting to use
that very talent...

718
01:14:03.372 --> 01:14:05.340
...against your will.

719
01:14:13.883 --> 01:14:15.145
Well...

720
01:14:17.920 --> 01:14:20.980
...he is a very willful boy.

721
01:14:23.392 --> 01:14:25.792
Indeed he is. Mr. Torrance.

722
01:14:25.995 --> 01:14:28.896
A very willful boy.

723
01:14:29.098 --> 01:14:30.429
A rather...

724
01:14:30.633 --> 01:14:32.157
...naughty boy...

725
01:14:32.368 --> 01:14:35.565
...if I may be so bold. sir.

726
01:14:42.812 --> 01:14:44.575
It's his mother.

727
01:14:46.716 --> 01:14:48.183
She...

728
01:14:48.384 --> 01:14:50.375
...interferes.

729
01:14:53.489 --> 01:14:56.583
Perhaps they need a good...

730
01:14:56.792 --> 01:14:58.384
...talking-to.

731
01:14:58.828 --> 01:14:59.658
lf...

732
01:14:59.862 --> 01:15:02.626
...you don't mind my saying so.

733
01:15:03.432 --> 01:15:05.059
Perhaps...

734
01:15:05.601 --> 01:15:07.296
...a bit more.

735
01:15:10.506 --> 01:15:11.734
My girls. sir...

736
01:15:11.941 --> 01:15:15.741
...they didn't care for
the Overlook at first.

737
01:15:16.412 --> 01:15:20.314
One of them actually stole
a pack of matches...

738
01:15:20.516 --> 01:15:23.178
...and tried to burn it down.

739
01:15:24.253 --> 01:15:25.914
But I...

740
01:15:26.122 --> 01:15:28.090
...corrected them. sir.

741
01:15:29.425 --> 01:15:33.555
And when my wife tried to prevent me
from doing my duty...

742
01:15:33.763 --> 01:15:35.025
...I...

743
01:15:36.031 --> 01:15:38.124
...corrected her.

744
01:15:48.144 --> 01:15:51.079
KDK 1 calling KDK 1 2.

745
01:15:51.380 --> 01:15:53.143
Are you receiving me?

746
01:15:56.352 --> 01:15:59.810
This is KDK 1 calling
KDK 1 2.

747
01:16:00.156 --> 01:16:02.954
KDK 1 calling KDK 1 2.

748
01:16:03.159 --> 01:16:04.820
Do you read me?

749
01:16:09.198 --> 01:16:12.224
This is KDK 1 calling
KDK 1 2.

750
01:16:12.434 --> 01:16:14.994
KDK 1 calling KDK 1 2.

751
01:16:15.204 --> 01:16:16.967
Are you receiving me?

752
01:17:04.887 --> 01:17:08.152
You're with Hal and Charlie
on Radio 63. KHOW. Denver.

753
01:17:08.357 --> 01:17:10.917
And we have a bad day out there.

754
01:17:11.126 --> 01:17:14.493
Heavy snow throughout
the Denver metro area.

755
01:17:14.697 --> 01:17:16.187
Many mountain passes...

756
01:17:16.398 --> 01:17:19.265
...Wolf Creek and Red Mountain
passes are closed...

757
01:17:19.468 --> 01:17:22.767
...and the chain law is in effect
at the Eisenhower Tunnel.

758
01:17:22.972 --> 01:17:24.633
We hear from the news department...

759
01:17:24.840 --> 01:17:28.037
...only a few flights are
landing at Stapleton Airport...

760
01:17:28.244 --> 01:17:29.836
...and with storms like this...

761
01:17:30.045 --> 01:17:34.175
...I guess the entire airport will
be closed within the hour.

762
01:17:34.350 --> 01:17:37.217
The storm will continue through
the day and the Weather Service...

763
01:17:37.419 --> 01:17:39.887
...has declared a stockman's
and traveler's advisory...

764
01:17:40.089 --> 01:17:42.887
...for all areas outlying
the Denver metro region.

765
01:20:34.263 --> 01:20:35.958
How do you like it?

766
01:20:42.571 --> 01:20:44.095
How do you like it?

767
01:20:54.049 --> 01:20:56.711
What are you doing down here?

768
01:21:01.090 --> 01:21:03.422
I just...

769
01:21:03.892 --> 01:21:04.916
...wanted...

770
01:21:05.360 --> 01:21:07.089
...to talk to you.

771
01:21:09.465 --> 01:21:10.727
Okay.

772
01:21:11.333 --> 01:21:12.800
Let's talk.

773
01:21:22.611 --> 01:21:24.602
What do you want to talk about?

774
01:21:32.521 --> 01:21:35.684
I can't really remember.

775
01:21:36.492 --> 01:21:38.619
You can't remember.

776
01:21:39.428 --> 01:21:40.759
No...

777
01:21:41.130 --> 01:21:42.529
...I can't.

778
01:21:47.836 --> 01:21:51.101
Maybe it was about Danny?

779
01:21:53.475 --> 01:21:56.171
Maybe it was about him.

780
01:21:59.815 --> 01:22:03.114
I think we should discuss Danny.

781
01:22:05.921 --> 01:22:07.718
I think...

782
01:22:08.123 --> 01:22:11.889
...we should discuss
what should be done with him.

783
01:22:16.598 --> 01:22:19.192
What should be done with him?

784
01:22:24.173 --> 01:22:25.970
I don't know.

785
01:22:26.475 --> 01:22:28.466
I don't think that's true.

786
01:22:28.677 --> 01:22:31.271
I think you have some
very definite ideas...

787
01:22:31.480 --> 01:22:33.175
...about what should be done
with Danny.

788
01:22:33.382 --> 01:22:35.976
And I'd like to know
what they are.

789
01:22:37.886 --> 01:22:39.683
Well. I...

790
01:22:39.988 --> 01:22:44.391
...I think maybe he should be taken
to a doctor.

791
01:22:44.593 --> 01:22:47.892
You think "maybe"
he should be taken to a doctor?

792
01:22:50.132 --> 01:22:53.465
When do you think "maybe"
he should be taken to a doctor?

793
01:22:54.102 --> 01:22:55.467
As soon as possible?

794
01:22:56.071 --> 01:22:58.403
"As soon as possible?"

795
01:23:01.076 --> 01:23:02.509
Please.

796
01:23:03.912 --> 01:23:07.177
You believe his health
might be at stake.

797
01:23:08.750 --> 01:23:10.274
Yes.

798
01:23:11.620 --> 01:23:14.248
And you are concerned about him.

799
01:23:16.825 --> 01:23:19.055
And are you concerned about me?

800
01:23:19.895 --> 01:23:21.055
Of course I am.

801
01:23:21.263 --> 01:23:23.493
Of course you are!

802
01:23:23.699 --> 01:23:26.827
Have you ever thought about
my responsibilities?

803
01:23:27.035 --> 01:23:28.525
What are you talking about?

804
01:23:28.737 --> 01:23:31.570
Have you ever had
a single moment's...

805
01:23:31.773 --> 01:23:33.832
...thought about
my responsibilities?

806
01:23:34.042 --> 01:23:36.306
Have you ever thought
for a single moment...

807
01:23:36.511 --> 01:23:39.309
...about my responsibilities
to my employers?!

808
01:23:39.581 --> 01:23:41.412
Has is ever occurred to you...

809
01:23:41.617 --> 01:23:45.109
...that I have agreed to look after
the hotel until May 1st?

810
01:23:45.354 --> 01:23:47.379
Does it matter to you at all...

811
01:23:47.589 --> 01:23:50.683
...that the owners have placed
their complete confidence in me...

812
01:23:50.892 --> 01:23:54.020
...and that I have signed
a letter of agreement...

813
01:23:54.229 --> 01:23:56.823
...in which I've accepted
that responsibility?

814
01:23:57.299 --> 01:23:59.324
Do you have the slightest idea...

815
01:23:59.534 --> 01:24:02.765
...what a moral and ethical
principal is? Do you?!

816
01:24:03.138 --> 01:24:06.232
Has it ever occurred to you what
would happen to my future...

817
01:24:06.441 --> 01:24:08.841
...if I fail to live up to
my responsibilities?

818
01:24:09.044 --> 01:24:11.342
Has it ever occurred to you?
Has it?!

819
01:24:11.546 --> 01:24:13.070
Stay away from me!

820
01:24:13.949 --> 01:24:15.007
Why?

821
01:24:15.317 --> 01:24:18.286
I just want to go back to my room.

822
01:24:18.487 --> 01:24:19.749
Why?

823
01:24:20.389 --> 01:24:21.253
Well...

824
01:24:22.391 --> 01:24:24.416
...I'm very confused.

825
01:24:25.560 --> 01:24:29.223
And I just need a chance
to think things over.

826
01:24:30.265 --> 01:24:34.201
You've had your whole fucking life
to think things over!

827
01:24:34.403 --> 01:24:37.167
What good's a few minutes more
going to do you now?

828
01:24:38.140 --> 01:24:39.630
Stay away from me!

829
01:24:39.975 --> 01:24:41.272
Please!

830
01:24:42.044 --> 01:24:43.102
Don't hurt me.

831
01:24:43.312 --> 01:24:44.643
I'm not going to hurt you.

832
01:24:44.846 --> 01:24:46.040
Stay away from me!

833
01:24:46.248 --> 01:24:47.112
Stay away!

834
01:24:47.316 --> 01:24:48.305
Darling.

835
01:24:48.517 --> 01:24:50.075
Light of my life.

836
01:24:50.519 --> 01:24:51.850
I'm not going to hurt you.

837
01:24:52.054 --> 01:24:54.045
You didn't let me finish
my sentence.

838
01:24:54.256 --> 01:24:56.451
I said.
"I'm not going to hurt you."

839
01:24:56.658 --> 01:24:59.422
I'm just going to bash
your brains in.

840
01:24:59.695 --> 01:25:02.664
I'm going to bash them
right the fuck in.

841
01:25:03.732 --> 01:25:05.290
Stay away from me!

842
01:25:05.801 --> 01:25:06.825
Stay away from me!

843
01:25:07.035 --> 01:25:09.435
I'm not going to hurt you.

844
01:25:09.705 --> 01:25:11.229
Stay away from me!

845
01:25:11.473 --> 01:25:12.531
Stay away!

846
01:25:13.408 --> 01:25:14.636
Please!

847
01:25:15.677 --> 01:25:17.440
Stop swinging the bat.

848
01:25:17.646 --> 01:25:18.908
Stay away from me.

849
01:25:19.681 --> 01:25:20.978
Put that bat down. Wendy.

850
01:25:21.183 --> 01:25:22.673
Stop it!

851
01:25:24.152 --> 01:25:25.278
Give me the bat.

852
01:25:25.487 --> 01:25:26.613
Please!

853
01:25:26.855 --> 01:25:29.050
- Stay away!
- Give me the bat.

854
01:25:29.257 --> 01:25:30.315
Stop it!

855
01:25:30.559 --> 01:25:31.992
Give me the bat.

856
01:25:32.327 --> 01:25:33.954
- Stay away from me.
- Stop swinging the bat.

857
01:25:34.162 --> 01:25:35.527
Please stop!

858
01:25:35.731 --> 01:25:36.925
Give me the bat.

859
01:25:37.132 --> 01:25:38.360
Stay away from me.

860
01:25:38.633 --> 01:25:40.999
- Stop it!
- Give me the bat.

861
01:25:42.404 --> 01:25:43.428
Goddamn...!

862
01:26:58.713 --> 01:27:00.408
What are you doing?

863
01:27:03.218 --> 01:27:04.685
Wait a minute.

864
01:27:06.087 --> 01:27:08.078
What are you doing?

865
01:27:10.926 --> 01:27:12.154
What are you doing?

866
01:27:26.041 --> 01:27:27.531
Wait a minute!

867
01:27:29.911 --> 01:27:31.503
What are you doing?

868
01:27:31.746 --> 01:27:33.475
Open the door!

869
01:27:34.783 --> 01:27:35.807
Goddamn it!

870
01:27:36.017 --> 01:27:39.578
Let me out of here!
Open the goddamn door!

871
01:27:43.291 --> 01:27:44.519
Wendy. listen.

872
01:27:44.960 --> 01:27:47.895
Let me out and I'll forget
the whole goddamn thing.

873
01:27:48.096 --> 01:27:50.564
It'll be just like
nothing ever happened.

874
01:28:05.247 --> 01:28:06.612
Baby.

875
01:28:07.816 --> 01:28:11.115
I think you hurt my head
real bad.

876
01:28:12.721 --> 01:28:14.382
I'm dizzy.

877
01:28:15.390 --> 01:28:17.585
I need a doctor.

878
01:28:24.466 --> 01:28:25.660
Honey.

879
01:28:28.336 --> 01:28:30.668
Don't leave me in here.

880
01:28:39.281 --> 01:28:41.181
I'm going to go now.

881
01:28:44.252 --> 01:28:46.083
I'm going to try...

882
01:28:46.288 --> 01:28:49.280
...to get Danny down
the Sidewinder...

883
01:28:49.991 --> 01:28:52.357
...in the Snowcat today.

884
01:28:54.596 --> 01:28:56.427
I'll bring back a doctor.

885
01:29:01.803 --> 01:29:03.668
I'm going to go now.

886
01:29:11.112 --> 01:29:14.912
You've got a big surprise
coming to you.

887
01:29:16.384 --> 01:29:18.978
You're not going anywhere.

888
01:29:20.655 --> 01:29:24.785
Go check out the Snowcat and the
radio. and you'll see what I mean.

889
01:29:29.397 --> 01:29:31.092
Go check it out.

890
01:29:33.234 --> 01:29:35.429
Go check it out!

891
01:29:38.807 --> 01:29:40.741
Go check it out.

892
01:31:28.583 --> 01:31:30.983
It's Grady. Mr. Torrance.

893
01:31:31.720 --> 01:31:33.688
Delbert Grady.

894
01:31:35.256 --> 01:31:36.848
Grady?

895
01:31:57.312 --> 01:31:59.143
Hello. Grady.

896
01:32:03.818 --> 01:32:05.615
Mr. Torrance...

897
01:32:07.555 --> 01:32:11.286
...I see you can hardly
have taken care of the...

898
01:32:12.026 --> 01:32:14.517
...business we discussed.

899
01:32:21.236 --> 01:32:24.171
No need to rub it in. Mr. Grady.

900
01:32:25.039 --> 01:32:29.100
I'll deal with that situation
as soon as I get out of here.

901
01:32:29.978 --> 01:32:32.708
Will you indeed. Mr. Torrance?

902
01:32:33.214 --> 01:32:35.045
I wonder.

903
01:32:36.217 --> 01:32:38.310
I have my doubts.

904
01:32:39.521 --> 01:32:43.753
l. and others. have come
to believe...

905
01:32:43.958 --> 01:32:46.950
...that your heart is not in this.

906
01:32:47.595 --> 01:32:50.120
That you haven't the belly for it.

907
01:32:56.304 --> 01:33:00.604
Just give me one more chance
to prove it. Mr. Grady.

908
01:33:01.442 --> 01:33:03.376
That's all I ask.

909
01:33:04.913 --> 01:33:09.179
Your wife appears to be stronger
than we imagined. Mr. Torrance.

910
01:33:09.384 --> 01:33:10.851
Somewhat more...

911
01:33:11.052 --> 01:33:13.020
...resourceful.

912
01:33:13.288 --> 01:33:16.052
She seems to have got
the better of you.

913
01:33:19.294 --> 01:33:21.956
For the moment. Mr. Grady.

914
01:33:22.697 --> 01:33:24.858
Only for the moment.

915
01:33:26.768 --> 01:33:30.932
I fear you will have to deal
with this matter...

916
01:33:31.206 --> 01:33:34.869
...in the harshest possible way.
Mr. Torrance.

917
01:33:35.443 --> 01:33:37.001
I fear...

918
01:33:37.278 --> 01:33:39.838
...that is the only thing to do.

919
01:33:43.318 --> 01:33:45.411
There's nothing
I look forward to...

920
01:33:45.620 --> 01:33:49.522
...with greater pleasure.
Mr. Grady.

921
01:33:50.925 --> 01:33:53.655
You give your word on that.
do you. Mr. Torrance?

922
01:33:55.129 --> 01:33:57.154
I give you my word.

923
01:35:09.270 --> 01:35:11.830
Redrum.

924
01:35:12.774 --> 01:35:15.334
Redrum.

925
01:37:23.304 --> 01:37:24.862
Danny. stop it!

926
01:38:21.662 --> 01:38:23.129
I'm home.

927
01:39:00.468 --> 01:39:03.335
Come out. come out.
wherever you are.

928
01:39:28.896 --> 01:39:30.761
I can't get out.

929
01:39:31.566 --> 01:39:32.692
Run!

930
01:39:33.534 --> 01:39:34.967
Run and hide!

931
01:39:35.503 --> 01:39:36.629
Run!

932
01:39:36.837 --> 01:39:38.065
Quick!

933
01:39:39.774 --> 01:39:44.302
Little pigs. little pigs.
let me come in.

934
01:39:50.051 --> 01:39:53.452
Not by the hair
on your chinny-chin-chin?

935
01:39:54.989 --> 01:39:57.048
Then I'll huff...

936
01:39:57.258 --> 01:39:59.158
...and I'll puff...

937
01:39:59.360 --> 01:40:01.419
...and I'll blow your house in!

938
01:40:16.344 --> 01:40:17.709
Please!

939
01:40:18.446 --> 01:40:20.209
Don't!

940
01:40:20.881 --> 01:40:22.405
Don't!

941
01:40:41.002 --> 01:40:42.230
Stop it!

942
01:40:46.474 --> 01:40:48.032
Here's Johnny!

943
01:43:30.104 --> 01:43:31.332
Hello?

944
01:43:36.777 --> 01:43:38.540
Anybody here?

945
01:44:00.634 --> 01:44:02.192
Hello?

946
01:44:14.515 --> 01:44:16.346
Anybody here?

947
01:44:46.313 --> 01:44:48.247
Anybody here?

948
01:45:29.256 --> 01:45:30.951
Danny-boy!

949
01:48:11.785 --> 01:48:13.719
I'm coming!

950
01:48:16.223 --> 01:48:18.157
I'm coming. Dan!

951
01:49:18.952 --> 01:49:21.352
Great party. isn't it?

952
01:49:39.006 --> 01:49:41.236
I'm coming!!

953
01:49:43.811 --> 01:49:46.109
You can't get away!

954
01:49:49.983 --> 01:49:52.383
I'm right behind you!

955
01:53:17.424 --> 01:53:19.449
- Mommy!
- Danny. come here!

956
01:53:20.660 --> 01:53:22.389
Mommy.

957
01:53:30.737 --> 01:53:32.136
Where...?
